{
  "texts": [
    "An example includes regulations mandating the exclusion of specific indicators that, while predicting some degree of social dangerousness, are directly or indirectly linked to ethnic or social background, e.g., the postal code (van Dijck, 2022).",
    "(e) Extrinsic risks.",
    "The risk of AIs for recidivism rate assessment would finally interact with extrinsic risk types.",
    "Some extrinsic risks, in this case, would be compliance risk, liability risk, and economic risk.",
    "Indeed, AI risk may be influenced by the lack of effective rules for the allocation of liabilities for adverse effects."
  ]
}